sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
This action adds a user to an existing group in Box account of the associated credentials.

Inputs:

  • User ID - The user id which will be added to the group specified by Group ID.
  • Group ID - The Group ID of the group where the member will be added to.
  • Role - The role of the user in the group. For e.g. member or admin.
  • Can Run Reports - Flag to allow group admin to run reports on activity for the group or the individual members of it. It is one of the group level permission.
  • Can Instant Login - Flag to allow group admin to instant Login to any members' account in this group. Does not apply to the admin or Co-admins of the account. It is one of the group level permission.
  • Can Create Account - Flag to allow allow group admin to add new user accounts from the Users tab. They will not be able to enable co-admin permissions, or delete users. It is one of the group level permission.
  • Can Edit Accounts - Flag to allow group admin to edit user accounts for the members in this group from the Users tab. They will not be able to enable co-admin permissions or delete users. Does not apply to the Admin or Co-admins of the account. It is one of the group level permission.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".
  • Type - Type of object created i.e. Group membership.
  • ID - ID of the group membership created.
  • User - User’s JSON representation that contains type, user ID, name and login.
  • Group - Group’s JSON representation that contains type, group ID and name.
  • Membership Details
    • - Membership Details
    • ID
    • User
    • Group

Error Messages:

  • Invalid username or password/token.
  • User with given ID not found.
  • Group with given ID not found.
  • User already exists in group.
  • Cannot assign configurable permissions to role type member.
  • The credentials associated with the Box Spoke connection does not have enough permission to perform this action.

Additional Note:

  • Group level permissions that are configured for Group members with "admin" role only. Members with "member" role will have null Group level permissions.

To use this action, the corresponding Box connection and credential must be created and associated with the Box Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.

  • Group ID - The Group ID of the group where the member will be added to.
  • Role - The role of the user in the group. For e.g. member or admin.
  • Can Run Reports - Flag to allow group admin to run reports on activity for the group or the individual members of it. It is one of the group level permission.
  • Can Instant Login - Flag to allow group admin to instant Login to any members' account in this group. Does not apply to the admin or Co-admins of the account. It is one of the group level permission.
  • Can Create Account - Flag to allow allow group admin to add new user accounts from the Users tab. They will not be able to enable co-admin permissions, or delete users. It is one of the group level permission.
  • Can Edit Accounts - Flag to allow group admin to edit user accounts for the members in this group from the Users tab. They will not be able to enable co-admin permissions or delete users. Does not apply to the Admin or Co-admins of the account. It is one of the group level permission.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".
  • Type - Type of object created i.e. Group membership.
  • ID - ID of the group membership created.
  • User - User’s JSON representation that contains type, user ID, name and login.
  • Group - Group’s JSON representation that contains type, group ID and name.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid username or password/token.
  • User with given ID not found.
  • Group with given ID not found.
  • User already exists in group.
  • Cannot assign configurable permissions to role type member.
  • The credentials associated with the Box Spoke connection does not have enough permission to perform this action.

Additional Note:

  • Group level permissions that are configured for Group members with "admin" role only. Members with "member" role will have null Group level permissions.

To use this action, the corresponding Box connection and credential must be created and associated with the Box Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
